cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO

This paper is about video object segmentation (VOS) using deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves designing a novel network architecture (MTN) to transfer masks between frames, which requires learning from data (cs.LG) and involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on datasets, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications.
